The party must replace Mmusi Maimane as both a parliamentary leader and a federal leader. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - As the DA tries to regroup following a slew of resignations, who's in the running to take over the reins? The party must replace Mmusi Maimane as both parliamentary leader and federal leader. The Federal Council will meet next month to elect Maimane's interim successor. READ: Maimane quits as DA leader Former DA Chief Whip John Steenhuisen is being lobbied to replace Maimane. The party’s KwaZulu-Natal leader, Zwakele Mncwango, is also eyeing the top job. While he previously denied having an interest in the position, Western Cape Premier Alan Winde is seen as a dark horse in the race.